article.headline: Denver 66, Arkansas State 65
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Erick Benzel scored 25 points, 19 of them in the second half, to set Denver up to edge out Arkansas State 66-65 Thursday night. Ryan Goral hit his only field goal of the game, a 3-pointer, with 7 seconds left on the clock to give Denver the one-point win. Arkansas State led 35-23 at halftime in a game that saw seven lead changes. But ASU did not hit a field goal in the final 5:03. Benzel hit 7-13 from behind the 3-point arc. Carvell McAlister added 17 points for Denver (10-6, 2-2 Sun Belt Conference). Rodney Billups dished out six assists. Arkansas State (11-6, 2-4) had three players in double figures, led by J.J. Montgomery with 22 points. Dewarick Spencer and Kim Adams each had 12 points, and Spencer grabbed eight rebounds and was credited with five assists. The Indians had a chance to win on a last-second layup by Spencer that bounced off the back of the rim.
